cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.LG 

The paper deals with reasoning about graph properties expressed as fixpoints of algebraic equations, which falls under the category of logic (cs.LO). It also involves separation logics, which is a subfield of programming languages (cs.PL). The focus on heap-based data structures and concurrency suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the use of mathematical foundations and proof techniques suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
